g:\mathbb{R}\rightarrow\mathbb{R}
C^2
\lim_{h\rightarrow 0}\dfrac{g(a+h)-2g(a)+g(a-h)}{h^2}=g''(a).
g
h>0
h_1\in(0,h)
g'
h_2\in(0,h_1)
g(a+h)-g(a)=h\cdot g'(a+h_1).
g'(a+h_1)-g'(a)=h_1\cdot g''(a+h_2).
g(a+h)-g(a)=hg'(a)+hh_1g''(a+h_2).
g(a+h)-g(a)=hg'(a)+\frac 1 2g''(a)h^2+o(h^2)
g(a-h)-g(a)=-hg'(a)+\frac 1 2g''(a)h^2+o(h^2)
h\to 0
g''(a)+\frac{o(h^2)}{h^2}\to g''(a)
